
[1]catechism

   CATECHISM, n.

   1. A form of instruction by means of questions and answers,
   particularly in the principles of religion.

   2. An elementary book containing a summary of principles in any science
   or art, but appropriately in religion, reduced to the form of questions
   and answers, and sometimes with notes, explanations, and references to
   authorities.
